{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἐπιστήμη</b>, ἡ, <br /> (ἐπίσταμαι) <b>acquaintance with</b> a matter, <b>understanding</b>, <b>skill</b>, as in archery, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Philoctetes” 1057; in war, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.121, 6.72, 7.62; ἐ. πρὸς τὸν πόλεμον 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 33.7 (perhaps to be read περί) περὶ τὰ μαθήματα 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Philebus” 55d; τοῦ νεῖν [prev. author] “Grg.” 511c \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐπιστήμῃ <b>skilfully</b>, οἱ μὴ ἐ. τοὺς ἐπαίνους ποιούμενοι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.AD: Plotinus Philosophus 5.5.13. \">Refs 3rd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3>. <b>professional skill</b>: hence, <b>profession</b>, οἱ τὴν ἰατρικὴν ἐ. μεταχειριζόμενοι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “PFay.” 106.22 (2nd c.AD)\">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; ζωγράφος τὴν ἐ. painter <b>by profession,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" POxy. 896.5 (4th c.AD). \">Refs 4th c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2>. generally, <b>knowledge</b>, ἐπιστήμῃ σύ μου προὔχοις ἄν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 1115 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; πάντ᾽ ἐπιστήμης πλέως full <b>of knowledge</b> in all things, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Ant.” 721, compare “Tr.” 338 \">Refs</a>]; ἐκ τῆς ἐ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Fragmenta” 522.3 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐ. δοξαστική, opposed to ἀλήθεια, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Sophista” 233c \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>plural</i>, <b>kinds of knowledge</b>, μυρίαι ἀνδρῶν ἐπιστᾶμαι πέλονται [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Bacchylides Lyricus 9.38, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Symposium” 208a. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3>. <b>scientific knowledge, science</b>, opposed to δόξα, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 477bf, 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “νόμος” 4, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Politicus” 301b, 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Anthologia Graeca” 0.88b30, “EN” 1139b18: coupled with ἐμπειρία and τέχνη, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 422c, compare “Ion” 536c, 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Metaphysica” 981a2 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>plural</i>, <b>the sciences</b>, frequently in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus (“R.” 522c, +others), etc. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G7454","accentedUnicode":"ἐπιστήμη","shortDef":"higher knowledge","mediumDef":"higher knowledge","stepGloss":"higher knowledge","stepTransliteration":"epistēmē","count":0,"_step_Type":"word"}]}